brewery.brewery_description:
Isley Brewing Company is the true definition of microbrewing. Owned by Richmond native Michael Isley,we opened our doors on October 26th, 2013.  Mike immediately hired head brewer Josh Stamps and began the brewing process on a three barrel brewhouse while fermenting in seven barrel fermenters. Our very first beer at Isley was 'The Bribe' - still our one and only 'flagship' beer - a delicious oatmeal porter that will quench your thirst and soothe your soul.
 
We started distribution within about three months of opening and have been in many restaurants in and around central Virginia. We've practiced controlled growth during our first year, slowly adding in additional fermentation 
space, and more kegs.
 
Our goal here at Isley is to embrace the talents of our
professional brewer with the passion commonly found in home brewing to create a true crafted beer.  Our intent is to think outside the box every time and push limits while not following the path that others tend to follow.  
 
Come try the fruits of our labor!

beer.beer_description: In collaboration with the Virginia Historical Society, we present "Charlotte Shandy".  We’ve taken inspiration from a handwritten recipe out of Charlotte County, Virginia, 1840.  This "Lemon Beer", is light, slightly sweet, crisp, and blended well on the finish.  Dryhopped for additional aromatics, and given a slightly higher carbonation level, this shandy is perfectly crushable for the end of summer.

2:30pm in the afternoon, 72 degrees, sunny, slight breeze and not a cloud in the sky.
'Plain Jane Blueberry' embodies that perfect day in a glass. With a scent of blueberries, this slightly spiced, light bodied Belgian White Ale will please your palette and your imagination.

It is said that death can take many forms, one of them a goat. In this form Hel comes for us all, however she can be bribed away with a bushel of oats.
This dark roasted oatmeal porter has notes of coffee and chocolate and was made to save your soul from Hel. Be sure you bribe her well...

There's no place like home, there's no place like home, there's no place like ... well maybe one place, Isley Brewing Co.! Here Ruby Red Slippers are more than just a fashion statement and a free ride home. We have taken our delightfully refreshing Session Pale Ale, The Man Behind The Curtain, a step beyond. With help from a few dedicated volunteers (You know who you are) we hand zested, chopped, and squeezed 200 Ruby Red Grapefruits. We then mix these in with the pale ale in a 7bbl stainless steel cocoon until this beer-terfly is ready to spread her wings. The grapefruit adds its own unique blend tart, citrus, sweet, and bitter to the New Zealand grown Motueka and Pacific Jade hops. This combination of fresh fruit and light ale makes Ruby Red Slippers the best day drinker this side of the Rainbow!

Can we just say HOT MESS and leave it at that … The ‘Root of All Evil’ ginger golden ale taps the inner goddess that all of us seek or desire ! It’s a little sweet, a little sassy… full of spice…yet refreshingly appealing.   The heavy malt base boosts the sweetness of this easy drinking beer while the low hop profile allows the spices to shine through. She’s got hints of lemon, orange and cinnamon but none of that can compare to the ½ pound per barrel of fresh, crushed ginger. 
‘The Root of All Evil’  -- a delicious way to welcome the warmer weather.

2:30pm in the afternoon, 72 degrees, sunny, slight breeze and not a cloud in the sky.
'Plain Jane' embodies that perfect day in a glass.
This slightly spiced, citrusy Belgian White Ale is full of flavor and will please your palette and your imagination.
Anything but plain….

A traditional Belgian dubbel, with the addition of organic pumpkin in the mash, and organic/fair trade spices from our RVA neighbors at Ellwood Thompsons Market in the kettle and the brite tank. Moderate carbonation creates a thick, creamy head,  and the use of dark candi sugar and Belgian crystal malts give the beer a complex, bready, malty backbone to support the heavy spice additions.  
Cheers!

Brewed in the traditional style, Our Irish Red is a balanced, easy drinking ale.  Prior to the invention of more controllable kilns, roasted malts and grain were used to give beers their red, copper, and brown color.  We’ve used just a touch of roasted barley to color our beer, and hopped it perfectly to balance the big malt backbone.  The beer pours a deep copper, and blends malty sweetness and mild hoppy bitterness together for a wonderful, crushable, Irish Red Ale.

This barrel aged Choosy Mother is the epitome of all that is good. The creamy mouth feel of our Oatmeal Peanut Butter Porter combined with the rich flavor of hand crafted local bourbon makes this beer an unforgettable experience.

"A wretched hive of scum and villainy", is how Obi-Wan Kenobi describes Mos Eisley. A spaceport on Tatooine, Mos Eisley is the gathering point for many of the galaxies' dregs. The Mos Eisley Cantina serves frothy libations to all manner of crooks, bounty hunters, Sith, and Jedi alike. Money is the only thing that matters here... 

Mos Eisley Brown Ale is a traditional brown ale, inspired by the barren expanses of Tatooine. Brewed with a careful blend of roasted and caramel malts, it seeks to quench the thirsts of those who live in the shadows. English yeast and hops provide an eclectic flavor profile, while letting the dark flavors of the malt peek out from within. This one will quench the thirst of the Galaxies' dark underbelly.

Due to overwhelming love for this one, it's the return of our Raspberry-infused Gose, a light, refreshingly fruited beer that is sure to please!

• • •

We've chosen to add copious amounts of raspberry puree, adding another layer of complexity to the beer. A low hop bitterness, combined with sour, sweet, tart, and salty flavors, all backed by a simple blonde wheat backbone.

beer.beer_name: This Ain't Kentucky Bourbon Barrel Aged Oatmeal Porter

beer.beer_description: Banana Peanut Butter Oatmeal Porter: Available 6/17/17

Our newest offering is a beer made with love. Our Brewmaster’s 2.5 year old daughter, Charlie, helped her daddy write this recipe, (Every keystroke was her hand) and has affectionately been referring to it as "CharliePA".  His nickname for her has always been Charlie Barley, so it only seemed appropriate.  

A light, golden colored ale, brewed with a touch of caramel malt for some balance.  We added lots of late kettle additions of Citra, Mosaic, and El Dorado, and have triple dry hopped the beer with a combination of the same varietals.
Big nose, big flavor, but a balanced bitterness.  Look for notes of Orange, Green Pepper, Melon, Lemon, Lime, Pineapple, and resin in the flavor and aroma.

Clocking in at 8% ABV, this American style Double IPA was brewed with ridiculous additions of juicy hops. Hopped 3 different times during and after fermentation, the high alcohol content is masked by the bright flavors and aromas of Citra, Mosaic, Pacific Jade, El Dorado, and Idaho 7. American Ale Yeast provides a clean finish, with a lingering hop bite. ROAR!

Up All Night is our coffee version of The Bribe Oatmeal Porter. Enjoy flavors of candied pecan, graham cracker, and black cherry compliment the already present notes of coffee and chocolate. We would like to thank Ironclad Coffee Roasters for supplying the Colombia Huila Los Naranjos San Agustin coffee beans that are used in creating the ’Up All Night’ Coffee Porter!!

An American styled DIPA, w/ balanced bitterness, medium to full bodied. The addition of oats and wheat in the mash gives the beer a smooth, creamy mouthfeel. Dextrose for elevated abv, and lactose for some added sweetness. Copiously hopped with citra, mosaic, el dorado, and Idaho 7 hops. Dryhopped 3 times, it's a big ol stinker.

It’s a light, refreshing American IPA with a hop profile that leaves you wanting more.
At only 5.5% ABV and 45 IBUs this multi hopped treat produces large citrus flavors and aromas and finishes dry, clean and crisp.

A light colored, juicy, stinky IPA, packed with as many hops as we could muster.  The base beer presents hazy, with a thick white head.   A fluffy mouthfeel is created by adjusting water chemistry, and adding oats and wheat to the mash.  After late kettle and whirlpool additions, The beer is dryhopped every day for 7 days of fermentation, and again while moving through brite and packaging.  With slightly lower carbonation, the Citra, Mosaic, and Huell Melon hops really shine.
A pale blonde ale, brewed with wheat, soured in the kettle for 4 days witn lactobacillus, and dry hopped twice with Mandarina Bavaria, and El Dorado hop varieties

We partnered with our good friends and neighbors Buskey Cider to craft a simple golden ale, minimally hopped, and brewed in a traditional fashion.Then we added roughly 100 gallons of fresh pressed juice, blending golden delicious, red delicious, and pink lady varietals. 49% juice, 51% wort, and American ale yeast bubbled away, and left us with a finished brew that we find quite unique. A strong, apple forward flavor, combined with a little sweetness from the malt, but balanced on the palate, with the dry finish of a cider.
Cranberry and cinnamin infused.
